#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Remote Frame Buffer protocol"
msgstr "Remote Frame Buffer protokol"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter provides a brief description of the Remote Frame Buffer "
"protocol used by &krdc; and by other compatible systems. If you are already "
"familiar with Remote Frame Buffer, you can safely skip this chapter."
msgstr ""
"Ovo poglavlje daje kratak opis Remote Frame Buffer protokola kojeg korisni "
"&krdc; i ostali kompatibilni sistemi. Ukoliko ste već upoznati sa Remote "
"Frame Buffer, možete sigurno preskočiti ovo poglavlje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The high level implementation of a system using the Remote Frame Buffer "
"protocol is known as Virtual Network Computer, or more often just as "
"<acronym>VNC</acronym>."
msgstr ""
"Visoki nivo implementacije sistema koji korisni Remote Frame Buffer protokol "
"je poznat kao Virtual Network Computer, ili češće samo kao <acronym>VNC</"
"acronym>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remote Frame Buffer (or <acronym>RFB</acronym> for short) is a simple "
"protocol for remote access to graphical user interfaces. It works at the "
"frame-buffer level, which roughly corresponds to the rendered screen image, "
"which means that it can be applied to all windowing systems (including X11, "
"&MacOS; and &Microsoft; &Windows;). Remote Frame Buffer applications exist "
"for many platforms, and can often be free re-distributed."
msgstr ""
"Remote Frame Buffer (ili kratko <acronym>RFB</acronym>) je jednostavi "
"protokol za udaljeni pristup za korisničke grafičke interfejse, koji grubo "
"odgovaraju na usluženu sliku zaslona (uključujući X11, &MacOS; i &Microsoft; "
"&Windows;). Remote Frame Buffer aplikacije postoje za mnoge platforme, i "
"često mogu biti besplatno redistribuirane."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the Remote Frame Buffer protocol, the application that runs on the "
"machine where the user sits (containing the display, keyboard and pointer) "
"is called the client. The application that runs on the machine where the "
"framebuffer is located (which is running the windowing system and "
"applications that the user is remotely controlling) is called the server. "
"&krdc; is the &kde; client for the Remote Frame Buffer protocol. &krfb; is "
"the &kde; server for the Remote Frame Buffer protocol."
msgstr ""
"U Remote Frame Buffer protokolu, aplikacija koja je pokrenuta na mašini gdje "
"korisnik sjedi(sadržavajući zaslon, tastaturu i miš) se naziva klijent. "
"Aplikacija koja je pokrenuta na mašini gdje je framebuffer smješten (koji "
"pokreče sistem prozora i aplikacija koje korisnik udaljeno kontroliše) se "
"naziva server. &krdc; je za &kde; klijent za Remote Frame Buffer protokol. "
"&krfb; je za &kde; server za   Remote Frame Buffer protokol."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It takes a reasonable amount of network traffic to send an image of the "
"framebuffer, so Remote Frame Buffer works best over high bandwidth links, "
"such as a local area network. It is still possible to use &krdc; over other "
"links, but performance is unlikely to be as good."
msgstr ""
"To zahtijeva razumnu količinu mrežnog saobraćaja da se pošalje slika "
"framebuffer-a, tako da  Remote Frame Buffer najbolje radi preko visoke "
"propusnosti linkova, kao što je lokalna mreža. Ipak je moguće koristiti "
"&krdc;  preko drugih linkova, ali su performanse riskantne da bi bile dobre."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &krdc;"
msgstr "Korištenje &krdc;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is very easy to use &krdc; - it has a simple interface, as shown in the "
"screenshot below."
msgstr ""
"Veoma je lako koristiti &krdc; - ima jednostavan interfejs, kao što je "
"prikazano na slici ispod."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here's a screenshot of &krdc;"
msgstr "Ovdje je slika zaslona &krdc;-a"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid "&krdc; main window"
msgstr "&krdc; glavni prozor"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:163
#, no-c-format
msgid "Connecting &krdc; to compatible servers"
msgstr "Povezivanje &krdc;  sa kompatibilnim serverima"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&krdc; is a client, and it needs to be used with compatible servers. There "
"are different ways to connect to those servers:"
msgstr ""
"&krdc; je klijent, i mora biti korišten sa kompatibilnim serverima. Nekoliko "
"je različitih načina da se poveže na te servere:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Directly typing the server name (or IP address) into the <guilabel>Connect "
"to:</guilabel> input."
msgstr ""
"Direktno kucajući ime servera (ili IP adresu) u <guilabel>Poveži se na:</"
"guilabel> ulaz."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By using an invitation that you received. &krfb; uses invitations, and can "
"send them by email."
msgstr ""
"Koristeći pozivnicu koju ste primili. &krfb; koristi pozivnice, i može ih "
"slati putem email-a."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "Let's look at each of these in turn."
msgstr "Pogledajmo svaki od njih još jednom."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:185
#, no-c-format
msgid "Server name entry"
msgstr "Unos imena servera"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you know the host name (or IP address) of the server you want to connect "
"to, you can enter it directly into the <guilabel>Connect to:</guilabel> "
"input."
msgstr ""
"Ako znate ime domaćina (ili IP adresu) servera sa kojim se želite povezati, "
"možete ga upisati direktno u <guilabel>Poveži se na:</guilabel> ulaz."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to connect to a machine named megan, which is running a "
"<acronym>VNC</acronym> server on screen 1 (5901), you can enter "
"<userinput>megan:1</userinput> or <userinput>megan:5901</userinput> and "
"choose <guilabel>vnc</guilabel> as the protocol in the drop down box."
msgstr ""
"Ako se želite povezati na mašinu koja se zove megan, na kojoj je pokrenut "
"<acronym>VNC</acronym> server na zaslonu 1 (5901), možete unijeti "
"<userinput>megan:1</userinput> ili <userinput>megan:5901</userinput> i "
"izabrati <guilabel>vnc</guilabel> kao protokol u opadajućem izborniku."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:200
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Entering a hostname into &krdc;</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Unošenje imena domaćina u &krdc;</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:206
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Entering a hostname into &krdc;</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Unošenje imena domaćina u &krdc;</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:212
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Similary, if you are using a <acronym>RDP</acronym> server on that machine, "
"you can enter <userinput>megan</userinput>. Choose <guilabel>rdp</guilabel> "
"as the protocol. <acronym>RDP</acronym> does not need the screen number to "
"be specified. If the server runs the <acronym>RDP</acronym> server not on "
"the default port, you may specify it in the following way: "
"<userinput>megan:3910</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Slično, ako koristite <acronym>RDP</acronym> server server na toj mašini, "
"možete unijeti <userinput>megan</userinput>. Izaberite <guilabel>rdp</"
"guilabel> kao protokol. <acronym>RDP</acronym> ne zahtijeva da broj zaslona "
"bude specificiran. Ako server ne pokrene <acronym>RDP</acronym> server na "
"zadanom ulazu , možete to specificirati na sljedeći način: "
"<userinput>megan:3910</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You need to enter an &URL; in percent encoded syntax, i.e. @ as %40, for "
"&eg; <userinput>username%40ad.domain.example</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Trebate unijeti &URL; sa postotkom šifrovanom sintaksom, i.e. @ as %40, for "
"&eg; <userinput>username%40ad.domain.example</userinput>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using an invitation"
msgstr "Korištenje pozivnice"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:227
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Within the &krfb; server application, it is possible to send invitations "
"over email (and in other ways, although email is the most useful). If you "
"receive this type of email invitation, you can just click on the link "
"provided in the mail. This will start &krdc; if it is not already running, "
"and connect to the server specified in the invitation."
msgstr ""
"Sa &krfb; server aplikacijom, moguće je slati pozivnice putem email-a (i na "
"druge načine, mada je email najkorišteniji). Ako primite ovu vrstu "
"pozivnice, kliknite na link  koji Vam je proslijeđen na mail. Ovo će "
"pokrenuti &krdc; ako nije već pokrenut, i povezati se na server specificiran "
"pozivnicom."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "What happens when you connect"
msgstr "Šta se dešava kada se povežete"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Notice: Before connecting, ensure that the target computer (server) is "
"available on the network and, if necessary, that its firewall has been "
"correctly configured or disabled."
msgstr ""
"Primijetite: Prije povezivanja, uvjerite se da je ciljani kompjuter (server) "
"dostupan na mreži i, ukoliko je potrebno, da mu je firewall ispravno "
"konfiguriran ili isključen."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No matter how you select the server to connect to, the next thing that "
"happens is that &krdc; asks you about the network connection to the server, "
"as shown below:"
msgstr ""
"Nebitno na koji način odaberete server za povezivanje, sljedeća stvar koja "
"će se desiti je da Vas &krdc; pita za povezivanje na server, kao što je "
"prikazano ispod:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>&krdc; connection speed selection</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>odabir brzine konekcije &krdc;</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&krdc; connection speed selection</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>odabir brzine konekcije &krdc;</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are three speed settings for the <acronym>VNC</acronym> protocol:"
msgstr "Postoje tri moguće postavke za <acronym>VNC</acronym> protokol:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"High Quality (LAN, direct connection), which is the default, and you should "
"evaluate how well this setting performs before selecting a lower performance "
"option that uses less bandwidth."
msgstr ""
"Visoki kvalitet (LAN, directno povezivanje), koje je zadano, i trebali biste "
"procijeniti koliko su dobre performanse ovih postavki prije nego odaberete "
"opciju slabijih performansi koje koriste manju propusnost."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:277
#, no-c-format
msgid "Medium Quality (DSL, Cable, fast Internet)."
msgstr "Srednji kvalitet (DSL, Kabl, brzi Internet)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:279
#, no-c-format
msgid "Low Quality (Modem, ISDN, slow Internet)."
msgstr "Niska kvaliteta (Modem, ISDN, spori Internet)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you always operate over the same link type, you can deselect the checkbox "
"labeled <guilabel>Show this dialog again for this host</guilabel>, which "
"means that you won't be asked about the connection type again for this host, "
"providing you identify it in the same way. For example, if a host has two "
"names, and deselect the checkbox when connecting using one name, you won't "
"get asked if you connect using that name, although you will be asked if you "
"use the other name, or the IP address."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You select the appropriate speed setting, and select the <guibutton>OK</"
"guibutton> to proceed."
msgstr ""
"Odaberite prikladne postavke brzine, i odaberite <guibutton>OK</guibutton> "
"da nastavite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can see the connection status in the icon in the tab."
msgstr "Možete vidjeti status povezivanja na ikoni na kartici."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on the configuration of the server, you may (and almost certainly "
"will) need to provide a password to authenticate to the server. &krdc; will "
"provide a password dialog similar to that shown below."
msgstr ""
"U ovisnosti od konfiguracije servera, možda ćete (a najvjerovatnije hoćete) "
"trebati unijeti šifru da potvrdite server. &krdc; će izbaciti mali dijalog "
"sa šifrom, kao što je prikazano ispod:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&krdc; has the ability to save the password for further connections to the "
"same host. It uses KWallet for doing this. You need to check the "
"<guibutton>Remember password (KWallet)</guibutton> check box if you like to "
"use this feature."
msgstr ""
"&krdc; ima mogućnosti da sačuva šifru za sljedeća povezivanja na istog "
"domaćina. Koristi KWallet za ovo. Trebate označiti <guibutton>Zapamti šifru "
"(KWallet)</guibutton> ukoliko želite koristiti tu mogućnost."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>&krdc; password entry</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&krdc; unos šifre</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:325
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&krdc; password entry</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&krdc; unos šifre</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After authentication, you will be connected to the remote server, and can "
"begin using &krdc; to observe or control the remote desktop."
msgstr ""
"Nakon provjere autenticnosti, bit ćete povezani sa udaljenim serverom, i "
"moći ćete početi koristiti &krdc; da posmatrate ili upravljati udaljenim "
"desktopom."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid "Controlling the remote desktop connection"
msgstr "Upravljanje vezom sa udaljenim desktopom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Having connected to the remote server, you would normally use the keyboard "
"and mouse to control the windowing system and applications on that remote "
"machine."
msgstr ""
"Kada se povežete sa udaljenim serverom, normalno ćete koristiti tastaturu i "
"miš da kontrolišete prozore i aplikacije na udaljenoj mašini."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:346
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can view the remote desktop either as a full screen, or as a window on "
"the local desktop. You can change between these modes using icons shown "
"below."
msgstr ""
"Udaljeni desktop možete pregledati na cijelom zaslonu, ili kao prozor na "
"lokalnom desktopu. Možete mijenjati između ovo dvoje korištenjem ikona koje "
"su prikazane ispod."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:354
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>&krdc; full screen mode selection</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&krdc; odabir prikaza preko cijelog zaslona</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&krdc; full screen mode selection</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&krdc;odabir prikaza preko cijelog zaslona</phrase>"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:368
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>&krdc; window mode selection</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&krdc; odabir pregleda preko prozora</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:374
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&krdc; window mode selection</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&krdc; odabir pregleda preko prozora</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:380
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Full screen mode is normally better when you are helping a remote user, "
"because you can see all of what they can see. Window mode is most useful "
"when you are working both remotely and locally - perhaps referring to some "
"local documentation and then using those instructions on the remote machine."
msgstr ""
"Prikaz preko cijelog zaslona je inače bolji kada pomažete udaljenom "
"korisniku, zato što tako možete vidjeti sve što oni vide. Pregled preko "
"prozora je najkorisniji kada paralelno radite i na udaljenom i na lokalnom "
"zaslonu - na primjer kada pozivajući se na neke lokalne dokumente koristite "
"te instrukcije na udaljenoj mašini."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:388
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using window mode"
msgstr "Korištenje prozora"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In window mode, you can terminate the connection by closing the window, by "
"clicking on the logout button."
msgstr ""
"Korištenjem prozora možete prekinuti vezu zatvaranjem prozora, pritiskom na "
"dugme za odjavu."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:397
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using full screen mode"
msgstr "Korištenje cijelog zaslona"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:399
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In full screen mode, you can change the appearance of the toolbar. The "
"transparency of the toolbar can be changed with scrollwheel."
msgstr ""
"Korištenjem prikaza preko cijelog zaslona, možete promijeniti prikaz na "
"alatnoj traci.  Prozirnost alatne trake može biti promijenjena na kotačiću "
"za listanje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:408
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmarks"
msgstr "Oznake"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:410
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&krdc; has the ability to manage bookmarks. If you need to connect often to "
"the same remote desktop, you can add an entry for this connection to the "
"bookmark list. You can do so with a click on <menuchoice><guimenu>Bookmarks</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Add Bookmark</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""
"&krdc; ima mogućnost za upravljanje oznakama. Ako trebate da se povežete sa "
"nekim udaljenim desktopom, možete dodati unos za ovu vezu u listu oznaka. To "
"možete uraditi klikom na <menuchoice><guimenu>Oznake</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Doraj oznaku</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:419
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>&krdc; bookmarks menu</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&krdc; izbornik oznaka</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:425
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>&krdc; bookmarks menu</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&krdc; izbornik oznaka</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:432
#, no-c-format
msgid "History Bookmarks"
msgstr "Historija oznaka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&krdc; saves last used remote desktop connections. You can access these "
"special bookmarks at <menuchoice><guimenu>Bookmarks</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>History</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Of course you can "
"also delete a bookmark of this list if you don't need it anymore in the "
"list. Just click <guibutton>Delete Bookmark</guibutton> which appears after "
"a click with the right mouse button on the bookmark you would like to delete."
msgstr ""
"&krdc; spašava posljednje korištene veze sa udaljenim desktopom. Ovim "
"posebnim oznaka možete pristupiti na <menuchoice><guimenu>Oznake</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Historija</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Naravno, oznake "
"sa ove liste možete i obrisati ukoliko ih ne trebate više na listi. Samo "
"kliknite dugme <guibutton>Obriši oznaku</guibutton> koje se pojavi nakon što "
"kliknete desno dugme miša na oznaku koju želite obrisati."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:446
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing &krdc; configuration"
msgstr "Upravljanje &krdc; konfiguracijom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure KRDC...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>, you can open a dialog to modify the behavior of "
"&krdc;. Selecting that button brings up a window as shown below:"
msgstr ""
"Korištenjem<menuchoice><guimenu>Postavke</guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriši "
"KRDC...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, možete otvoriti dijalog da podesite "
"ponašanje &krdc;. Odabirom tog dugmeta pojavit će se prozor kao što je "
"prikazano ispod:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid "&krdc; preferences - General tab"
msgstr "&krdc; postavke - kartica Općenito"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:461
#, no-c-format
msgid "&krdc; preferences - <guilabel>General</guilabel> tab"
msgstr "&krdc; postavke - kartica <guilabel>Općenito</guilabel>"

